19/01/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov and Vice President Angel Marin took the oath for their second term in office at a ceremony in parliament Friday (January 19th).
In his address to the nation, Parvanov vowed to work for the country's national interests as a NATO and EU member.
He also urged the government to remember that Bulgaria must comply with its commitments to the Union.
Parvanov defeated the ultranationalist leader of the Attack party, Volen Siderov, in a runoff on October 29th, becoming Bulgaria's first-ever re-elected president.
(Mediapool, News.bg, bTV - 19/01/07)
